16. nomina dabant: Roman colonists were not adventurers: commissioners were appointed deducendae coloniae, and citizens ‘gave in their names’ at Rome as volunteers. They were con- ducted to their destination like an army, sub uexillo, and formed a garrison of the place where they settled. The colonia was a town, not a colony in our sense of the word.
